    <p>A gentle heat caressing your lips with a velvet custard centre and a warmth of cinnamon. A perfect bite. Possibly, the best dessert ever?</p>
 

<p>Named as one of the best 50 things to eat in the world according to The Guardian. Past√©is de Nata, also know as Portuguese custard tart, is an egg tart pastry dusted. Created by the Catholic monks and nuns of Saint Mary of Bethlehem, in Lisbon.</p>

<p>The tarts are made from the discarded egg yolks since the egg whites were used for starching their fairs and habits. From then on, baking and selling these tarts became a way of generating income for the monasteries.</p>


